Description:
This program is an implementation of the non-rigid point set registration 
algorithm presented in the following ICCV'05 paper:
 A Robust Algorithm for Point Set Registration Using Mixture of Gaussians, 
 Bing Jian and Baba C. Vemuri,
 10th IEEE International Conference on Computer Vision (ICCV 2005),
 17-20 October 2005, Beijing, China, pp. 1246-1251.

If you use this program in a scholarly work, please make a proper citation
to this paper. A bibtex entry for this paper is given below:
@INPROCEEDINGS{Jian&Vemuri_iccv05,
	author = {Bing Jian and Baba C. Vemuri},
	title = {A Robust Algorithm for Point Set Registration Using Mixture of Gaussians.},
	booktitle = {10th IEEE International Conference on Computer Vision (ICCV 2005), 17-20 October 2005, Beijing, China},
	year = {2005},
	pages = {1246-1251}
}


Demos in Windows command line, MATLAB and Python are available:
1. Windows executable
 gmmreg_tps config.ini  
 (please see the comments in the provided example ini files)

2. Matlab demo scripts
 gmmreg_demo('./fish_half.ini');
 gmmreg_demo('./face.ini');

3. Python demo scripts
import gmmreg
gmmreg.run('./fish_full.ini')
gmmreg.run('./fish_half.ini')
(matplotlib is required for plotting the point sets)


